  "original_title": "\u0db7\u0dcf\u0dab\u0dca\u0da9 \u0db8\u0dd2\u0dbd \u0d85\u0da9\u0dd4 \u0d9a\u0dbb\u0db1\u0dca\u0db1 \u0d9a\u0dcf\u0dbd\u0dba \u0d95\u0db1 - \u0dc0\u0dd9\u0dc5\u0db3 \u0d87\u0db8\u0dad\u0dd2",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Time is needed to reduce commodity prices - Trade Minister",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Trade Minister Mr. Naleen Fernando said that he knows that the manufacturers and sellers of goods keep a bigger profit than the cost and since the price of the goods is 100 percent higher, it will take some time to take measures for this.",
        "Commenting on the measures being taken regarding the abnormal increase in the prices of imported and domestically produced food and beverages, the Minister mentioned this when he opened a Sathosa shop in Batuwatta area.",
        "Further commenting here, the minister said that since the price of goods is very high, as the Minister of Trade, he and the government will take steps to provide essential materials at a low price and firstly, the goods will be made available in the market and secondly, they will look into reducing the prices of the goods within this month.",
        "He also mentioned that as the government, including the President, will present a program to provide relief to the people in the next few months, the next interim budget will not give much priority to the development of the country.",
        "The Minister also stated that the work of the Consumer Service Authority under the Ministry of Trade has been in a state of failure for the past time and since its four hundred investigating officers are unable to provide the necessary service to the consumers, a program to start consumer protection committees at the level of the regional secretariats of the island will start next week. and will do.",
        "Also, Minister Naleen Fernando pointed out that there is a situation where the quality of the materials as well as the prescribed weight are not there, but the institutions that should act in this regard are not working.",
        "The minister stated that the heads of the institutions that are unable to provide the necessary services for the customers by the institutions under the Ministry of Trade should leave, and the former director general of the Consumer Service Authority has been informed to leave and the secretary of the ministry has been appointed to work in that position."
      ],
